3D Cybersecurity Explainer Video - MVP Implementation

Core Files to Create:
index.html - Main HTML structure with Three.js integration
src/cybersecurity-3d.js - Main 3D scene logic and animation controller
src/characters.js - Alice, Bob, and Hacker 3D models/representations
src/network.js - Network nodes, message packet, and routing visualization
src/security-controls.js - 5 security defense animations (encryption, auth, integrity, firewall, endpoint)
src/audio-manager.js - Sound effects and timing coordination
src/styles.css - UI styling and responsive design
src/script-manager.js - Dialogue timing and subtitle management

Key Features:
3D scene with network topology visualization
Animated message packet traveling through network nodes
Character representations (Alice, Bob, Hacker)
6 distinct scenes with smooth transitions
Interactive play/pause controls
Subtitle display for accessibility
Sound effects and visual cues
Responsive design for different screen sizes
Technical Implementation:
Three.js for 3D rendering and animations
GSAP for smooth transitions and timing
Web Audio API for sound effects
CSS Grid/Flexbox for UI layout
Vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)


Scene Breakdown:
Hook (0-15s): Introduce characters and question
Travel (15-30s): Show message hopping through network
Intercept (30-45s): Hacker intercepts message with alarm
Consequences (45-60s): Rapid visual consequences
Defense Demo (60-120s): 5 security controls in sequence
Wrap (120-150s): Safe delivery and final message


Color Scheme:
Network: Cool blues (#2563eb, #3b82f6)
Attacker: Red/black (#dc2626, #1f2937)
Safe/Success: Green (#16a34a, #22c55e)
UI: Dark theme with accent colors